section.def:
inspector
                (督察) means an inspector of police of whatever
            grade or rank;

paragraph.content:
the Public Service (Disciplinary) Regulation made under section
                        21 of that Order (and together with that Order published as S.S. No. 5 to Gazette No. 2/1997);
                    and

subparagraph.content:
for the purposes only of the Pension Benefits Ordinance (Cap. 99), deemed to have retired from the public
                        service in accordance with section 11(1)(g) of that Ordinance;
                        or

subsection.def:
acquire
                    (取得) means acquire by purchase or by any
                other lawful means;

paragraph.content:
facilities that are not chargeable to the general revenue, including
                        holiday premises and recreational facilities (whether provided free or for a
                        charge);

social, educational and recreational activities and performances
                        (whether provided free or for a charge and whether provided for
                        participation or as spectator events);

subsection.def:
corporation
                    (法團) means the corporation sole constituted
                under section 39A(1);

paragraph.content:
whose contract of service with the police force has expired on or after
                        the person reached 55 years of age without the contract being
                        renewed;

whose contract of service as a police officer has expired on or after
                        the person reached 55 years of age without the contract being
                        renewed;

subsection.def:
function
                    (職能) includes a power, an authority and a
                duty;

paragraph.content:
all fees collected from social, educational and recreational activities
                organized by or on behalf of the Commissioner for the purposes of that
                Fund;

if a Police Staff Purchase Scheme is established under section
                        39F, undertaking transactions for the purpose of giving effect to the
                    Scheme;

may dispose of property derived from the application of the Police Welfare
                    Fund that is, in its opinion, no longer required for the purposes of that Fund;
                    and
